<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
There i go, Pwylw, matter/mind sorcerer actually on Mordred, the PvP server (in beta phase 2).<P>I never tried matter way for a sorcerer before Mordred, but i wanted to give it a try. <BR>First impression: Matter really needs a revamp. (but everyone know that.)<P>PvE wise, being a sorcerer on Mordred, a server with no boundaries, is really funny. There are so many things you can charm in Albion, Hibernia and Midgard, so many different and interesting monsters. Leveling is as easy as ever, you can go pretty much everywhere and with the new regen code, you are set. <BR>At level 9? oh, hunting blackthorns in hibernia.<BR>At level 18? oh, hunting blodfelag in midgard.<BR>Really great, really interesting!<P><BR>PvP wise, it's another song. First, you need to remember that every player will act as if yellow when you try to dot/blast/mez. This means even a grey can resist and even a grey can hit you bad. But of course this also means that you can mez purple players easier and you can actually blast them quite nicely. The only real actual problem for sorcerers is that pets do not follow this new rule. That means your pet will insta kill greys and won't be able to hit anything on purples. I think this has to change since it's not fair at all for pet classes, but the answer is now in Mythic's hand.<P>But i'm here to talk about matter spec sorcerers in PvP server right? Well, let be frank, matter sucks. At 28, with just enough in Mind to charm the new pets, i find myself using my base dot(55 to 61 x 4, one tick per 5 seconds) rather than the spec one(29 to 35 x6, one tick per 4 seconds), which is not too cool. Since my body is at 1 (+x), i drain from 30 to 140ish, draining a lot of power in the process...<BR>Don't get me wrong, i'm pretty effective in PvP. I poison, stick the pet, run, root, re-poison, run. Rince & repeat. However, the penalty of poisoning (you can't really mez or root a poisoned person) is not balanced by a better damaging power.<P><BR>Overall, after 2 weeks on Mordred, lots of fun, lots of monsters to charm and i hate skalds and high level runemasters  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>I was trying to get 29 to charm the Alp lucradan in hibernia (they disease, snare), but since the snare is not working anymore, my new goal is 32 for the bandits mages and their bolts.<P><BR>If any sorcerer got questions about PvP server, feel free  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P><B>Pwylw</B>[SUN]<BR>Matter Sorcerer<BR><I>"He who Dots better buy new boots"</I>
</FONT>
