Against Theurgist, it really depends on who finds who first. If you are surprised by a theurgist, he will be able to cast 2 or 3 pets on you before you can do anything. Best solution in such situation, if you are fast enough, is to 1) stick the pet on the caster and 2) quickcast AE mez on the theurgist pets. If you find the theurgist first, just stick your pet on him, dot and blast. If he uses quickcast to mez/root your pet, he will die to your dot/blast and if he quickcast on you, he will die to your pet.<P>Alp luacra are nice because of the snare, which is REALLY good against meleers. They really suck in PVE (not enough hp), but in PvP, they are quite nice.<BR>I tested Werewolf warders lately (they root and melee nicely) and they proved to be very useful in PvP. <BR>I can't charm bandit mage yet, but that will be the best pet i can have i think, both for PvP and PvE.<P>The pets are still not following the new PvP code (where all players are yellow to you) and it's driving me crazy.<P>Another problem emerged with matter sorc. My alliance captured 2 power relics, which should give all damage spells a 20% boost. Alas, this is only effective on Direct Damage spells, leaving me shitty as usual.<P><BR>One thing for sure now, i will be body/mind...<P>--------------------<P><B>Pwylw</B>[SUN]<BR>Matter Sorcerer<BR><I>"He who Dots better buy new boots"</I>
